<br>
What could have been done different that would have caused less loss of life to Iraqi civilians, including children?  Do you honestly believe those children all locked away in that prison had a reasonable chance of surviving to ever get out?  How many children were locked up compared to the number who lost their lives or become wounded due to the battle?  I have only seen the same 8-10 children in all the press footage around the world.  I saw over 50 children pour out of that prison (and thats only one prison). <br>
<br>
What about the kids who were locked in that 4th unit of that other prison, the one where people who didnt pay got stuck in the 4th unit and all were guaranteed to pretty much wind up dead?  There were thirteen and fourteen year olds in that one. <br>
<br>
I sure hope none of you are for partial birth abortion, because thats killing children for absolutely no good.  They are fully functional children.  Now thats a real crime. Hate for you all to be real hypocrites on that.  <br>
<br>
So back to the question: <br>
What could have been done different to cause less loss of life by Iraqi's and to make the middle east a more peaceful region? <br>
<br>
You know, Vellks brought up Israel/Palestine issues (of which I have said since this whole thing started threads ago I feel needs to be dealt with..funny how Velks missed that).  So, question there: <br>
How would Saddam still being around and paying 25k to each and every Palestinian suicide bomber help make getting peace there easier?  <br>
<br>
Also, on that issue, some of you may have forgotten:<br>
1) Before Sept 11th, Palestine/Israel was a priority for Bush. We were very close to having Palestine regain its lands.  <br>
2) Sept 11th happened and Bush had to deal with Afghanistan and then follow up on Iraq (which had been a campaign promise pretty much from before this all happened. It didnt just come up.)  Sharon received harsh words during this time at first from Bush, but then as Bush needed political capital to carry out Afghanistan and Iraq, it had to go to the back burner for a minute. <br>
3) Now that Afgh and Iraq major parts are done, Bush is once again returning his focus to Israel and Palestine.  <br>
4) Whats being going on in Israel/Palestine during this time will not continue on much longer now that Sharon cant hide behind our other conflicts easily anymore. <br>
5) Sharon was an opportunist and he is still trying, unfortunately, he is just pissing of the US even more by assuming that Bush will just go along like many presidents before<br>
6) Sharon needs to realize that Republicans have been less his friends then Democrats and start watching himself -- Republicans arent as dependent on the Jewish political money and capital as the Democrats (no harm to Bush) so Sharon could end up alienating his two key allies in the world (Britain and US), both of which want him to stop this @#%$ now. <br>
